# gameConfig.ts

Single source of truth for all game dimensions and feel.

## Key sections

- `canvas` — Phaser game size (also in `main.ts`)
- `table.playWidth/Height`, `wallThickness`, `goal.width/depth`
- `ball.radius`, `bounce`, `drag`, `maxSpeed`
- `stick.slideSpeed`, `slideMode` (`smooth`|`snap`), `rotateSpeed`
- `players.player1.sticks[]` — `role`, `pawnCount`, `bumperTop/Bottom`, `xOffset`
- `players.player2` — getter, mirrored from player1
- `input.columns` — `stickIndex` + `keys.top/middle/bottom`

## Bumper math

```
minSlideY = playTop + bumperTop * playHeight
maxSlideY = playBottom - bumperBottom * playHeight
```

## Pawn spacing

`computePawnOffsets(count, rodSpan)` in `utils/spacing.ts` — equal distribution along rod.

## Mirror

`getMirroredPlayerConfig(player1)` flips `side` and `xOffset` for player2. Edit player1 only.
